																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">5</div> <div class="vers-content">And there were two of the ancients of the people appointed judges that year, of whom the Lord said: Iniquity came out from Babylon from the ancient judges, that seemed to govern the people.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">5</div> <div class="vers-content">There came a year in which those two elders of the people were appointed judges, of whom the Lord said, Wickedness has sprung up in Babylon, and the roots of it are those elders and judges who claim to rule the people. </div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">6</div> <div class="vers-content">Isti frequentabant domum Joakim, et veniebant ad eos omnes qui habebant judicia.</div></div></td>
