																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">there was a throng of people in Joakimâ€™s house, and the two elders were there, intent upon their malicious design against Susannaâ€™s life.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Et dixerunt coram populo: Mittite ad Susannam filiam HelciÃ¦ uxorem Joakim. Et statim miserunt.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">And they said before the people: Send to Susanna daughter of Helcias the wife of Joakim. And presently they sent.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">They asked publicly that Susanna, daughter of Helcias and wife to Joakim, should be sent for; sent for she was,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">Et venit cum parentibus, et filiis, et universis cognatis suis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">And she came with her parents, and children, and all her kindred.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">and came out with her parents and her children and all her kindred.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">Porro Susanna erat delicata nimis, et pulchra specie.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">Now Susanna was exceeding delicate, and beautiful to behold.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">So dainty she was, and so fair,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">At iniqui illi jusserunt ut discooperiretur (erat enim cooperta), ut vel sic satiarentur decore ejus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">But those wicked men commanded that her face should be uncovered, (for she was covered,) that so at least they might be satisfied with her beauty.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">these two knaves would have her let down her veil, the better to enjoy the sight of her charms.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Flebant igitur sui, et omnes qui noverant eam.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Therefore her friends and all her acquaintance wept.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">All her friends, all her acquaintances, were in tears.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">Consurgentes autem duo presbyteri in medio populi, posuerunt manus suas super caput ejus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">But the two elders rising up in the midst of the people, laid their hands upon her head.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">Then the two elders rose amidst the throng, and laid their hands upon Susannaâ€™s head,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">QuÃ¦ flens suspexit ad cÃ¦lum: erat enim cor ejus fiduciam habens in Domino.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">And she weeping looked up to heaven, for her heart had confidence in the Lord.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">while she, weeping, looked up to heaven, in token that her heart had not lost confidence in the Lord.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">Et dixerunt presbyteri: Cum deambularemus in pomario soli, ingressa est hÃ¦c cum duabus puellis: et clausit ostia pomarii, et dimisit a se puellas.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">And the elders said: As we walked in the orchard alone, this woman came in with two maids, and shut the doors of the orchard, and sent away the maids from her.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">We were walking in the garden apart, said the elders, when this woman came out with two hand-maidens. She had the garden door shut close, and sent the maidens away;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">37</div> <div class="vers-content">Venitque ad eam adolescens, qui erat absconditus, et concubuit cum ea.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">37</div> <div class="vers-content">Then a young man that was there hid came to her, and lay with her.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">37</div> <div class="vers-content">whereupon a young man, who had been in hiding till then, came out and had his will with her.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">38</div> <div class="vers-content">Porro nos cum essemus in angulo pomarii, videntes iniquitatem, cucurrimus ad eos, et vidimus eos pariter commisceri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">38</div> <div class="vers-content">But we that were in a corner of the orchard, seeing this wickedness, ran up to them, and we saw them lie together.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">38</div> <div class="vers-content">We, from a nook in the garden, saw what foul deed was being done, and ran up close, so that we had full view of their dalliance;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">39</div> <div class="vers-content">Et illum quidem non quivimus comprehendere, quia fortior nobis erat, et apertis ostiis exilivit:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">39</div> <div class="vers-content">And him indeed we could not take, because he was stronger than us, and opening the doors he leaped out:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">39</div> <div class="vers-content">but lay hold of the man we could not; he was too strong for us, opening the garden door and springing out.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">40</div> <div class="vers-content">hanc autem cum apprehendissemus, interrogavimus, quisnam esset adolescens, et noluit indicare nobis: hujus rei testes sumus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">40</div> <div class="vers-content">But having taken this woman, we asked who the young man was, but she would not tell us: of this thing we are witnesses.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">40</div> <div class="vers-content">The woman we caught, and asked her who her gallant was, but she would not tell us. To all this, we bear witness.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">41</div> <div class="vers-content">Credidit eis multitudo quasi senibus et judicibus populi, et condemnaverunt eam ad mortem.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">41</div> <div class="vers-content">The multitude believed them as being the elders and the judges of the people, and they condemned her to death.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">41</div> <div class="vers-content">They were elders, they were judges of the people, and they persuaded the assembly, without more ado, to pass the death sentence.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">42</div> <div class="vers-content">Exclamavit autem voce magna Susanna, et dixit: Deus Ã¦terne, qui absconditorum es cognitor, qui nosti omnia antequam fiant,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">42</div> <div class="vers-content">Then Susanna cried out with a loud voice, and said: O eternal God, who knowest hidden things, who knowest all things before they come to pass,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">42</div> <div class="vers-content">Whereupon Susanna cried aloud, Eternal God, no secret is hidden from thee, nothing comes to pass without thy foreknowledge.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">43</div> <div class="vers-content">tu scis quoniam falsum testimonium tulerunt contra me: et ecce morior, cum nihil horum fecerim, quÃ¦ isti malitiose composuerunt adversum me.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">43</div> <div class="vers-content">Thou knowest that they have borne false witness against me: and behold I must die, whereas I have done none of these things, which these men have maliciously forged against me.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">43</div> <div class="vers-content">Thou knowest that these men have borne false witness against me; wilt thou let me die, a woman innocent of all the charges their malice has invented?</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">44</div> <div class="vers-content">Exaudivit autem Dominus vocem ejus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">44</div> <div class="vers-content">And the Lord heard her voice.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">44</div> <div class="vers-content">And the Lord listened to her plea;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">45</div> <div class="vers-content">Cumque duceretur ad mortem, suscitavit Dominus spiritum sanctum pueri junioris, cujus nomen Daniel:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">45</div> <div class="vers-content">And when she was led to be put to death, the Lord raised up the holy spirit of a young boy, whose name was Daniel.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">45</div> <div class="vers-content">even as she was being led off to her death, all at once he roused to utterance the holy spirit that dwelt in a young boy there, called Daniel.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">46</div> <div class="vers-content">et exclamavit voce magna: Mundus ego sum a sanguine hujus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">46</div> <div class="vers-content">And he cried out with a loud voice: I am clear from the blood of this woman.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">46</div> <div class="vers-content">This Daniel raised his voice and cried out, I will be no party to the death of this woman;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">47</div> <div class="vers-content">Et conversus omnis populus ad eum, dixit: Quis est iste sermo, quem tu locutus es?</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">47</div> <div class="vers-content">Then all the people turning themselves towards him, said: What meaneth this word that thou hast spoken?</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">47</div> <div class="vers-content">and when all the people turned upon him, asking what he meant,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">48</div> <div class="vers-content">Qui cum staret in medio eorum, ait: Sic fatui filii IsraÃ«l, non judicantes, neque quod verum est cognoscentes, condemnastis filiam IsraÃ«l?</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">48</div> <div class="vers-content">But he standing in the midst of them, said: Are ye so foolish, ye children of Israel, that without examination or knowledge of the truth, you have condemned a daughter of Israel?</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">48</div> <div class="vers-content">he stood there in their midst, and said, Are you such fools, men of Israel, as to condemn an Israelite woman without trial, without investigation of the truth?</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">49</div> <div class="vers-content">revertimini ad judicium, quia falsum testimonium locuti sunt adversus eam.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">49</div> <div class="vers-content">Return to judgment, for they have borne false witness against her.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">49</div> <div class="vers-content">Go back to the place of judgement; the witness they have borne against her is false witness.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">50</div> <div class="vers-content">Reversus est ergo populus cum festinatione, et dixerunt ei senes: Veni, et sede in medio nostrum, et indica nobis: quia tibi Deus dedit honorem senectutis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">50</div> <div class="vers-content">So all the people turned again in haste, and the old men said to him: Come, and sit thou down among us, and shew it us: seeing God hath given thee the honour of old age.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">50</div> <div class="vers-content">Eagerly enough the people went back, and the elders would have Daniel sit with them, such credit God had given him beyond his years.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">51</div> <div class="vers-content">Et dixit ad eos Daniel: Separate illos ab invicem procul, et dijudicabo eos.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">51</div> <div class="vers-content">And Daniel said to the people: Separate these two far from one another, and I will examine them.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">51</div> <div class="vers-content">He bade them part the two men, at a distance from each other, while he questioned them.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">52</div> <div class="vers-content">Cum ergo divisi essent alter ab altero, vocavit unum de eis, et dixit ad eum: Inveterate dierum malorum, nunc venerunt peccata tua, quÃ¦ operabaris prius:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">52</div> <div class="vers-content">So when they were put asunder one from the other, he called one of them, and said to him: O thou that art grown old in evil days, now are thy sins come out, which thou hast committed before:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">52</div> <div class="vers-content">So parted they were, and when the first was summoned, thus Daniel greeted him: Grown so old in years, and years ill spent! Now, that past sinning of thine has found thee out,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">53</div> <div class="vers-content">judicans judicia injusta, innocentes opprimens, et dimittens noxios, dicente Domino: Innocentem et justum non interficies.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">53</div> <div class="vers-content">In judging unjust judgments, oppressing the innocent, and letting the guilty to go free, whereas the Lord saith: The innocent and the just thou shalt not kill.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">53</div> <div class="vers-content">a man that perverts justice, persecutes innocence, and lets the guilty go free. Has not the Lord said, Never shalt thou put the innocent man, the upright man, to death?</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">54</div> <div class="vers-content">Nunc ergo, si vidisti eam, dic sub qua arbore videris eos colloquentes sibi. Qui ait: Sub schino.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">54</div> <div class="vers-content">Now then, if thou sawest her, tell me under what tree thou sawest them conversing together. He said: Under a mastic tree.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">54</div> <div class="vers-content">Thou foundest her; good; they met under a tree; tell us what kind of tree. And he answered, Under a mastic-tree I surprised them.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">55</div> <div class="vers-content">Dixit autem Daniel: Recte mentitus es in caput tuum: ecce enim angelus Dei, accepta sententia ab eo, scindet te medium.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">55</div> <div class="vers-content">And Daniel said: Well hast thou lied against thy own head: for behold the angel of God having received the sentence of him, shall cut thee in two.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">55</div> <div class="vers-content">The right word! cried Daniel; prized asunder thyself shall be, when God bids his angel requite thee for this calumny.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">56</div> <div class="vers-content">Et, amoto eo, jussit venire alium, et dixit ei: Semen Chanaan, et non Juda, species decepit te, et concupiscentia subvertit cor tuum:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">56</div> <div class="vers-content">And having put him aside, he commanded that the other should come, and he said to him: O thou seed of Chanaan, and not of Juda, beauty hath deceived thee, and lust hath perverted thy heart:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">56</div> <div class="vers-content">Then he had this one removed, and bade the other come near. Brood of Chanaan, said he, and no true son of Juda, so beauty ensnared thee? So lust drove thy heart astray?</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">57</div> <div class="vers-content">sic faciebatis filiabus IsraÃ«l, et illÃ¦ timentes loquebantur vobis: sed filia Juda non sustinuit iniquitatem vestram.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">57</div> <div class="vers-content">Thus did you do to the daughters of Israel, and they for fear conversed with you: but a daughter of Juda would not abide your wickedness.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">57</div> <div class="vers-content">Such approaches you have made, long since, to women of the other tribes, and they, from very fear, admitted your suit; but you could not bring a woman of Juda to fall in with your wicked design.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">58</div> <div class="vers-content">Nunc ergo, dic mihi sub qua arbore comprehenderis eos loquentes sibi. Qui ait: Sub prino.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">58</div> <div class="vers-content">Now therefore tell me, under what tree didst thou take them conversing together. And he answered: Under a holm tree.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">58</div> <div class="vers-content">And now tell me, under what tree it was thou didst find them talking together? Under a holm-oak, said he, I saw them.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">59</div> <div class="vers-content">Dixit autem ei Daniel: Recte mentitus es et tu in caput tuum: manet enim angelus Domini, gladium habens, ut secet te medium, et interficiat vos.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">59</div> <div class="vers-content">And Daniel said to him: Well hast thou also lied against thy own head: for the angel of the Lord waiteth with a sword to cut thee in two, and to destroy you.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">59</div> <div class="vers-content">The right word again! cried Daniel. Saw thee asunder the angel of the Lord will, with the sharp blade he carries yonder; you are both dead men.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">60</div> <div class="vers-content">Exclamavit itaque omnis cÅ“tus voce magna, et benedixerunt Deum, qui salvat sperantes in se.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">60</div> <div class="vers-content">With that all the assembly cried out with a loud voice, and they blessed God, who saveth them that trust in him.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">60</div> <div class="vers-content">And with that, the whole multitude cried aloud, blessing God that is the deliverer of those who trust in him.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">61</div> <div class="vers-content">Et consurrexerunt adversus duos presbyteros (convicerat enim eos Daniel ex ore suo falsum dixisse testimonium), feceruntque eis sicut male egerant adversus proximum,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">61</div> <div class="vers-content">And they rose up against the two elders, (for Daniel had convicted them of false witness by their own mouth,) and they did to them as they had maliciously dealt against their neighbour,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">61</div> <div class="vers-content">And they turned on the two elders, by Danielâ€™s questioning self-convicted of false witness; served they must be as they would have served others,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">62</div> <div class="vers-content">ut facerent secundum legem Moysi. Et interfecerunt eos, et salvatus est sanguis innoxius in die illa.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">62</div> <div class="vers-content">To fulfil the law of Moses: and they put them to death, and innocent blood was saved in that day.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">62</div> <div class="vers-content">and the law of Moses obeyed; so they put them to death. That day, an innocent life was saved.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">63</div> <div class="vers-content">Helcias autem et uxor ejus laudaverunt Deum pro filia sua Susanna cum Joakim marito ejus, et cognatis omnibus, quia non esset inventa in ea res turpis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">63</div> <div class="vers-content">But Helcias and his wife praised God, for their daughter Susanna, with Joakim her husband, and all her kindred, because there was no dishonesty found in her.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">63</div> <div class="vers-content">Good cause had Helcias and his wife to praise God for their daughter Susanna, good cause had Joakim and all his friends; no breath of suspicion assailed her now.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">64</div> <div class="vers-content">Daniel autem factus est magnus in conspectu populi a die illa, et deinceps.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">64</div> <div class="vers-content">And Daniel became great in the sight of the people from that day, and thenceforward.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">64</div> <div class="vers-content">And as for Daniel, he was in high favour with all the people from that day forward.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">65</div> <div class="vers-content">Et rex Astyages appositus est ad patres suos, et suscepit Cyrus Perses regnum ejus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">65</div> <div class="vers-content">And king Astyages was gathered to his fathers, and Cyrus the Persian received his kingdom.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">65</div> <div class="vers-content">When king Astyages became part of his line, it was Cyrus, the Persian, succeeded him.  </div></div></td>
